description.narrative: By 2016 management teams at department level and managers of local health networks have capacity for analyzing the situation of health, planning and monitoring of results for equity., which contributes to Child Health, Child Protection And Emergencies, Health And Emergencies, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Sanitation, Wash And Emergencies, Water. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2016, children (boy and girls) from 0 to 6 years of age in the six priority departments, particularly those from population groups exposed to vulnerable situations, have greater access to integrated early childhood development services.
